Judicial Compensation Act
Judicial Compensation Regulation
[Last amended December 31, 2024 by B.C. Reg. 83/2023
and includes amendments by B.C. Reg. 39/2024]

Definition
1  In this regulation, "Act" means the Judicial Compensation Act.

Setting higher amounts for purposes of the Act
2  For the purposes of section 7.1 (2) of the Act, the following amounts are set:

(a)for paragraph (a) of that subsection, $40 000;

(b)for paragraph (b) of that subsection, 85% of the costs over $40 000 but under $150 000.

Repealed
3  Repealed. [B.C. Reg. 83/2023, s. 3.]

[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: Judicial Compensation Act, S.B.C. 2003, c. 59, s. 7.1 (3).]
